Lasomin is a &lt;a href="village"&gt;village&lt;/a&gt; in the administrative district of &lt;a href="Gmina%20Siennica"&gt;Gmina Siennica&lt;/a&gt;, within &lt;a href="Mi%C5%84sk%20County"&gt;Mińsk County&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Masovian%20Voivodeship"&gt;Masovian Voivodeship&lt;/a&gt;, in east-central Poland. It lies approximately south-west of &lt;a href="Siennica%2C%20Mi%C5%84sk%20County"&gt;Siennica&lt;/a&gt;, south of &lt;a href="Mi%C5%84sk%20Mazowiecki"&gt;Mińsk Mazowiecki&lt;/a&gt;, and south-east of &lt;a href="Warsaw"&gt;Warsaw&lt;/a&gt;.
